main event: A letter requesting identification of an unidentified object was sent to the President.
interesting points: The unidentified object was determined to be the satellite Echo I.
The sighting was reported in Budd Lake, New Jersey on June 8, 1963.
The sighting was classified as 'Insuff. Info. to Det.', meaning insufficient information to determine the nature of the object.
The Air Force responded to the letter, indicating that the object was the satellite Enos moving in an easterly direction.
The report is from the Project Blue Book files, which was the Air Force's program to investigate UFO sightings.
